outputs:
{"answer": "iDQ is a glitch detection pipeline. It utilizes glitch features in auxiliary channels generated in real-time to construct supervised-learning training sets from recent data labeled by witnessing noise in the target channel. This information is then used to automatically train various ML algorithms to identify glitches in the target channel. 

iDQ operated in real-time throughout the first three LIGO-Virgo observing runs, providing probabilistic statements about the presence of glitches in LIGO data and their auxiliary witnesses. It also demonstrated its ability to rapidly identify and confirm the presence of astrophysical signals, such as the GW170817 BNS event.

Sources: data\2011.01958v1.pdf, data\Cuoco_2021_Mach._Learn.__Sci._Technol._2_011002.pdf, data\1904.08693v2.pdf"}

